<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <title>CareerCompass User Guide</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'user_guide', media: 'all' %> <!-- Link to CSS for styling -->
</head>
<body>
  <section class="user-guide">
    <h1>CareerCompass User Guide</h1>
    
    <div class="intro">
      <p>This user guide will walk you through how to use the CareerCompass platform. Here, you can search for courses, compare them, and visualise key data like employment rates, salaries, and more!</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#creating-account">Creating an Account</a></li>
      <li><a href="#searching-courses">Searching for Courses</a></li>
      <li><a href="#bookmarking-courses">Bookmarking Courses</a></li>
      <li><a href="#comparing-courses">Comparing Courses</a></li>
      <li><a href="#visualising-trends">Visualising Trends</a></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="section" id="creating-account" style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
      <h3>1. Creating an Account</h3>
      <p>To use the platform, you need to create an account. Here's how:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Click on the 'Create Account' button on the homepage.</li>
        <li>Enter a valid email address and a secure password.</li>
        <li>You will be logged in immediately using your credentials.</li>
        <li>If you forget your password, we will send you a password reset link to your registered email address.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="section" id="searching-courses" style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
      <h3>2. Searching for Courses</h3>
      <p>To search for courses offered by various institutions, follow these steps:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Enter a keyword (e.g., "Computer Science") in the search bar.</li>
        <li>Optionally, you can filter by institution, faculty, employment rate or salary range.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="section" id="bookmarking-courses" style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
      <h3>3. Bookmarking Courses</h3>
      <p>Bookmark courses that you are interested in for easy access later:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>While viewing course details, click on the 'Bookmark' icon.</li>
        <li>Access your bookmarks from the 'Bookmarks' tab in your profile.</li>
        <li>You can save up to 5 courses in your bookmarks.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="section" id="comparing-courses" style="background-color: #e0e0e0;">
      <h3>4. Comparing Courses</h3>
      <p>To compare multiple courses:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Navigate to the 'Compare Courses' section.</li>
        <li>Select up to 5 courses from your bookmarks.</li>
        <li>Choose the comparison metrics, such as employment rate or salary.</li>
        <li>The system will display a side-by-side comparison of the selected courses.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="section" id="visualising-trends" style="background-color: #f0f0f0;">
      <h3>5. Visualising Trends</h3>
      <p>To visualise data trends over time for a selected course:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Select a course from your bookmarks.</li>
        <li>Choose the metrics you'd like to see over time (e.g., employment rate, salary).</li>
        <li>The system will generate an interactive chart showing trends across years.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</body>
</html>
